              "aggregated_output": "---\nname: cad-sim-pipeline\ndescription: \"Use for satellite thermal simulation modeling workflows that turn a spacecraft BOM into CAD geometry, COMSOL thermal simulation, ParaView visualization, analysis, and suggestions through apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline; also use for resuming runs, debugging run_root artifacts, logs, progress, and the 8-stage CAD-to-simulation pipeline.\"\n---\n\n# CAD Simulation Pipeline\n\nUse this skill for satellite thermal simulation modeling tasks in `apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline`: running the BOM-to-CAD-to-COMSOL/ParaView chain, resuming from a failed stage, inspecting `run_manifest.json`, or debugging missing artifacts under a `run_root`.\n\n## Guardrails\n\n- Default to `comsol_local` for normal runs so satellite thermal simulations produce real COMSOL artifacts. By default, let the pipeline auto-start/manage mphserver; use an existing mphserver only when it is already known to be listening.\n- Use `mock_contract` only for fast CLI smoke tests or contract validation where COMSOL execution is intentionally skipped.\n- Do not delete or recreate a `run_root` unless the user explicitly asks for a clean run.\n- Do not skip required predecessor stages unless the required files already exist and `run_manifest.json` or logs prove the predecessor completed.\n- When a single-step command fails on prerequisites, fix the missing predecessor stage or artifact before rerunning that step.\n\n## Workspace Resolution\n\n- Treat the pipeline `run_root` as the workspace root for this skill. All stage directories (`01_layout`, `02_geometry_edit`, `03_simulation`, `logs`, and later outputs) are resolved only under that workspace.\n- Before running or resuming a command, resolve and report the workspace root. Use this priority order:\n  1. CLI `--run-root /path/to/workspace`.\n  2. `RUN_ROOT=/path/to/workspace` when using `apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh`.\n  3. The wrapper default `/data/lbk/codex_web/FreeCAD_data/v7_data` only when neither of the above is supplied.\n- Resolve the BOM input independently using this priority order:\n  1. CLI `--bom-json /path/to/real_bom.json`.\n  2. `BOM_JSON=/path/to/real_bom.json` when using the wrapper.\n  3. The wrapper default only for local smoke/manual runs.\n- Never infer the workspace from the process `cwd`, the repository root, the skill directory, or a similarly named directory. If the user gives relative paths, expand them to absolute paths before checking artifacts or running commands.\n- For FreeCAD rebuilds inside `geometry-edit`, the FreeCAD workspace defaults to the same resolved pipeline `run_root` unless `--freecad-workspace-dir` is explicitly passed. Keep these two roots aligned unless the user has a specific reason to separate them.\n- Inspect `<run_root>/run_manifest.json`, `<run_root>/logs/progress_percentages.json`, and `<run_root>/logs/*.json` only after the workspace root is resolved. Do not search broadly for another run unless the resolved workspace is missing and the user asks you to locate one.\n- Do not pass `--connect-existing-mphserver` unless `CONNECT_EXISTING_MPHSERVER=1` is set and a COMSOL mphserver is known to be listening on the configured port.\n\n## Commands\n\nRun from the repo root. The shell wrapper sets the expected Python and `PYTHONPATH` defaults:\n\n```bash\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh run-all\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh layout-generate\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh geometry-edit\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh simulation\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh field-export\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh postprocess\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh case-build\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh analysis\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh suggestion\n```\n\nDirect Python form:\n\n```bash\nPYTHONPATH=/tmp/codex_openpyxl_py313 /data/conda/bin/python -m apps.bom_external_tools_pipeline.cli run-all --bom-json <real_bom.json> --run-root <run_root> --simulation-backend comsol_local\n```\n\nOmitting the command is equivalent to `run-all` for backward compatibility.\n\nWrapper argument rules:\n\n- `run_pipeline.sh simulation --run-root ...` runs only `simulation`.\n- `run_pipeline.sh --skip-postprocess` remains a full `run-all` invocation with that option.\n- Prefer environment variables for common paths: `BOM_JSON=<path> RUN_ROOT=<path> SIMULATION_BACKEND=comsol_local apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh run-all`.\n- `--connect-existing-mphserver` is ignored by the shell wrapper unless `CONNECT_EXISTING_MPHSERVER=1` is set. This prevents accidental `Connection refused` failures when no COMSOL mphserver is already listening on port 2036.\n\n## Stage Order And Inputs\n\n1. `layout-generate`: needs `--bom-json`; writes `01_layout`, `logs/layout_generate_stage_result.json`, and `logs/layout_generate_raw_result.json`.\n2. `geometry-edit`: needs completed `layout_generate` plus `logs/layout_generate_raw_result.json`; writes `02_geometry_edit` and geometry stage logs.\n3. `simulation`: needs completed `geometry_validate` and the complete after-state artifact set in `02_geometry_edit`, including `geometry_after.step`, `geometry_after.geom.json`, `geometry_after.layout_topology.json`, `simulation_input.json`, and `comsol_inputs/*`.\n4. `field-export`: needs completed `simulation_run` and `03_simulation/status.json`, `field_samples.json`, `tensors.json`; writes normalized field files into `04_postprocess`.\n5. `postprocess`: needs completed `field_export` and `04_postprocess/field_stats.json`; writes render and visualization manifests.\n6. `case-build`: needs completed `postprocess`; writes `05_case_build/component_index.json` and case artifacts.\n7. `analysis`: needs completed `case_build`; writes `06_analysis` reports.\n8. `suggestion`: needs completed `analysis` and `05_case_build/component_index.json`; writes `07_suggestions`.\n\nEach successful single-step command updates `run_manifest.json` without dropping unrelated existing stages. If prerequisites are missing, the CLI exits with a message naming missing stages or files.\n\n## Triage Checklist\n\n1. Read `<run_root>/run_manifest.json` and note the last completed stage.\n2. List `<run_root>/logs` and compare logs with the expected stage order.\n3. For the desired next command, verify its required predecessor stage and required files.\n4. If `simulation` is using the wrong STEP file, inspect the `02_geometry_edit` after-state companion files.\n5. Rerun the earliest missing or failed subcommand, then continue forward one stage at a time.\n\n## Recommended Workflows\n\nDefault satellite thermal simulation run:\n\n```bash\nBOM_JSON=<real_bom.json> RUN_ROOT=<run_root> SIMULATION_BACKEND=comsol_local apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh run-all\n```\n\nResume after a failed stage:\n\n```bash\nRUN_ROOT=<existing_run_root> apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh <stage-name>\n```\n\nRun with local COMSOL:\n\n```bash\nSIMULATION_BACKEND=comsol_local apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh simulation\n```\n\nFast smoke test without COMSOL:\n\n```bash\nRUN_ROOT=/tmp/bom_pipeline_smoke SIMULATION_BACKEND=mock_contract apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh run-all\n```\n\nConnect to an already running mphserver only when you have started and verified one:\n\n```bash\nCONNECT_EXISTING_MPHSERVER=1 SIMULATION_BACKEND=comsol_local apps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh simulation --connect-existing-mphserver\n```\n\nStop after simulation for COMSOL or ParaView triage:\n\n```bash\napps/bom_external_tools_pipeline/run_pipeline.sh --skip-postprocess\n```\n\n## Debugging Notes\n\n- Inspect `<run_root>/run_manifest.json` first; then check `<run_root>/logs/*.json`.\n- `geometry-edit` depends on the raw layout log, not only the layout stage summary.\n- `simulation` uses `02_geometry_edit/geometry_after.step` and fails fast if the complete after-state companion files such as `geometry_after.geom.json`, `geometry_after.layout_topology.json`, `geometry_after_registry.json`, `sample.yaml`, `simulation_input.json`, and `comsol_inputs/*` are missing.\n- Use `comsol_local` for normal satellite thermal simulation runs. Use `mock_contract` only for CLI smoke tests and contract validation; do not pass `--connect-existing-mphserver` unless a server is already listening on the configured port.\n\nCommon fixes:\n\n- Missing `logs/layout_generate_raw_result.json`: rerun `layout-generate`.\n- Missing `geometry_validate`: rerun `geometry-edit` after confirming layout logs exist.\n- Missing `03_simulation/status.json`, `field_samples.json`, or `tensors.json`: rerun `simulation`.\n- Missing `04_postprocess/field_stats.json`: rerun `field-export`.\n- Missing `05_case_build/component_index.json`: rerun `case-build`.\n- Missing `02_geometry_edit/geometry_after.step` or companion files: rerun `geometry-edit` to regenerate the complete after-state artifact set.\n- COMSOL `Connection refused` on port 2036: rerun without `--connect-existing-mphserver`, or start a COMSOL mphserver first and set `CONNECT_EXISTING_MPHSERVER=1` before passing that flag.\n",
